detaileddescription.para: NOW defines the value for scheduling an object immediately, even replacing the current SimProcess. Since the value is otherwise arbitrary as long as it is unique and can not be confused with any other legal or illegal (negative) value, it is set to be the constant defined in java.lang.Double and in java.lang.Float representing a non-number value.

detaileddescription.para: Returns a new simtime object with a time value representing the absolute difference of the time values of the given simtime objects. Note that since no negative time values are allowed, null will be returned if the result of the subtraction would have resulted in a negative value. That is, a's time value is smaller than b's.

detaileddescription.para: Checks if the two simtime parameters describe the same point of simulation time. Note that this is a static method available through calling the class SimTime i.e. SimTime.isEqual(a,b) where a and b are valid simtime objects.

simplesect.para: boolean : True if both parameters describe same point of simulation time

detaileddescription.para: Checks if the first of two points of simulation time is larger than the second. Larger means, that the time value of simtime a is larger and hence "later" than simtime b. Note that this is a static method available through calling the class SimTime i.e. SimTime.isLargerThan(a,b) where a and b are valid simtime objects.

simplesect.para: boolean : True if a is larger (later) than b

detaileddescription.para: Checks if the first of two points of simulation time is larger or equal to the second. Larger means, that the time value of simtime a is larger and hence "later" than simtime b. Equal means, that they both describe the same point in simulation time. Note that this is a static method available through calling the class SimTime i.e. SimTime.isLargerOrEqual(a,b) where a and b are valid simtime objects.

simplesect.para: boolean : True if a is larger (later) or equal to b

detaileddescription.para: Checks if the two simtime parameters describe the different points of simulation time. Note that this is a static method available through calling the class SimTime i.e. SimTime.isNotEqual(a,b) where a and b are valid simtime objects.

simplesect.para: boolean : True if parameters describe different points of simulation time

detaileddescription.para: Checks if the first of two points of simulation time is smaller than the second. Smaller means, that the time value of SimTime a is larger and hence "sooner" than simtime b. Note that this is a static method available through calling the class SimTime i.e. SimTime.isLargerThan(a,b) where a and b are valid simtime objects.

simplesect.para: boolean : True if a is smaller (sooner) than b

detaileddescription.para: Checks if the first of two points of simulation time is smaller or equal to the second. Smaller means, that the time value of simtime a is smaller and hence "sooner" than simtime b. Equal means, that they both describe the same point in simulation time. Note that this is a static method available through calling the class SimTime i.e. SimTime.isSmallerOrEqual(a,b) where a and b are valid simtime objects.

simplesect.para: boolean : True if a is smaller (sooner) or equal to b

xrefdescription.para: Represents points in simulation time. Is used to indicate points in simulation time at which the state of the model changes. Each point in simulation time is represented by an individual object of this class and offers its own methods for arithmetic operations. Ensures that only valid points of time are generated.
